  "story": {
    "intro": [
      "Every evening the great bell of Tollhollow rang the town to sleep. Tonight, for the first time in three hundred years, it made no sound at all.",
      "Something crept out of the crypt and swallowed the bell's echo. Pip, the junior bellkeeper, lights a lantern and starts down the stairs."
    ],
    "levelIntros": [
      "The Underhalls: moss, dust, and doors that lock themselves. The stolen echo passed this way. You can feel it humming in the stones.",
      "The Deep Crypt: the old bellkeepers rest here. Step softly, borrow bravely, and give the bones no reason to gossip.",
      "The Echo Chamber: the stolen sound coils below like a sleeping storm. One more staircase, little keeper. Ring true."
    ],
    "bossIntro": "The Echo Warden unfolds from the dark, wearing your bell's voice like a crown. It will not give the sound back. Take it.",
    "victory": [
      "The echo rushes up the stairwell, and far above, the bell laughs itself back to life. DONG. Tollhollow wakes up grinning.",
      "Pip climbs into the morning light: deafened, delighted, and very much promoted to Senior Bellkeeper."
    ],
    "defeat": [
      "The dark keeps its quiet a little longer. Up in Tollhollow, someone lights a candle in the silent tower and waits for you.",
      "Every bellkeeper falls a few times on the stairs. Catch your breath, relight the lantern, and go win back the sound."
    ]
  },
